sentences.english: Just as I start to turn back home I hear it: the soft, two-toned whistle of chickadees .
sentences.chinese: 就在我轉身要回去時，我聽到了兩聲輕輕的山雀啼叫。

sentences.english: Southern united states chickadee similar to the blackcap but smaller.
sentences.chinese: 產於美國南部的山雀，與黑冠雀形似但較小。

sentences.english: Mother looked, woodpeckers physicians see small tits fly over.
sentences.chinese: 循聲望去，啄木鳥醫師看到是小山雀飛過來了。

sentences.english: Virtually every day I'll hear a western tanager.
sentences.chinese: 幾乎每一天我聽到西方山雀。

sentences.english: I found a flock of long-tailed tits in the mountain.
sentences.chinese: 我在山裏看到了一羣銀喉長尾山雀。

sentences.english: Having said that, the titmouse flew away.
He took the titmouse home and raised it in a bamboo cage.
sentences.chinese: 他把山雀帶回家，放在一個竹籠裏飼養。

sentences.english: Under weaves of moonlight, blue tit's dream tickles.
sentences.chinese: 月光波來，藍山雀之夢爲之顫然。

sentences.english: A long-tailed tit alighted on the branch.
sentences.chinese: 一隻長尾山雀飛落在樹枝上。

sentences.english: "Tell me the weight of a snowflake, "a titmouse asked a wild dove.
sentences.chinese: “告訴我雪花有多重，”一隻山雀問一隻野鴿子。

sentences.english: Chickadees store collections of seeds, insects and spiders in the bark of trees or under leaves.
sentences.chinese: 山雀貯存種子，還有樹皮和樹葉下面的昆蟲，蜘蛛。

sentences.english: These girls are smoking hot with great big tits.
sentences.chinese: 這些女孩吸菸熱一對大山雀。

sentences.english: The owl was so startled to discover someone watching it hunt that it dropped the titmouse, which fell to the ground.
sentences.chinese: 貓頭鷹發現有人在看它捕獵，受到驚嚇，丟下了山雀。

sentences.english: Yang Pao ran over and picked the titmouse up， brushing away the ants.
sentences.chinese: 楊寶跑過去，拾起山雀，撣去螞蟻。

sentences.english: Today we have a great Big Tit Cream Pie.
sentences.chinese: 今天，我們有一個偉大的大山雀奶油餡餅。

sentences.english: It was so dazed it just lay there without moving.
sentences.chinese: 那隻山雀被摔昏了，躺在地上一動不動。
